|
:INFO
Shading Technique for Depth
Move the tip in small circular motions for smooth gradients rather than back-and-forth \
lines. Build shade in layers rather than burning dark in one pass. You can always go \
darker but you cannot go lighter once burned. Leave the palest areas untouched and

:NOTE
Transfer Your Design Without Graphite Contamination
Graphite pencil lines burn into the wood and become permanent. \
Use a water-soluble pen or transfer paper made for pyrography instead. \
Alternatively, tape a printed design face-down and trace over it \
with a ballpoint pen to transfer without graphite. \
Erase any remaining marks with a white eraser before you begin burning.

